flowchart TD
    A[Start: Add Prompt Format Rules] --> B[Read workflow-delegation.md]
    B --> C[Identify insert position after 4-layer template section]
    C --> D[Insert Format Rules section with TOON+MD hybrid spec]
    D --> E[Add contamination guard to Common Constraints]
    E --> F[Verify total line count]
    F --> G{Line count <= 200?}
    G -- Yes --> H[Validate Mermaid/TOON syntax]
    H --> I[End: File updated]
    G -- No --> J[Trim or split content to stay within limit]
    J --> F

## decisions

- insert-position: after 4-layer template section -- Format Rules logically extends delegation templates; placing it adjacent avoids readers missing the rule
- contamination-guard-location: Common Constraints block -- Every delegation call passes through Common Constraints, so the guard catches all outbound prompts
- hybrid-spec-granularity: per-format bullet list not prose -- Bullet list is machine-parseable and avoids ambiguity that prose introduces for LLM consumers
- line-count-loop: loop back to verify after trim -- A single trim pass may not suffice if multiple sections were added; re-check guarantees the invariant
- decision-node-shape: diamond for 200-line check -- Standard flowchart convention; decision nodes use rhombus to signal branching logic
- scope-single-file: modify workflow-delegation.md only -- Minimizes blast radius; cross-file changes require separate task to keep review atomic
